nse" and offers a new view of the relationship between God and his creatures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aFree will and determinismxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aGood and evilxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aTheodicy. 4aPsychology : Psychology of Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Christianity. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791485309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791485309/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles